plu\u0107a |url=https://www.dnevnik.ba/vijesti/prvi-slucaj-koronavirusa-u-grudama-zarazeni-muskarac-ima-tesku-upalu-pluca |website=Dnevnik.ba |accessdate=26 March 2020 |language=hr |date=25 March 2020}}</ref> [[Posu\u0161je]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Prvi slu\u010daj koronavirusa registrovan u Posu\u0161ju, zara\u017eena 33-godi\u0161njakinja |url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/prvi-slucaj-koronavirusa-registrovan-u-posusju-zarazena-33-godisnjakinja/200328150 |website=Klix.ba |accessdate=28 March 2020 |language=bs-BA}}</ref> [[\u0160iroki Brijeg]]<ref>{{cite web |title=U \u0160irokom Brijegu potvr\u0111en prvi slu\u010daj koronavirusa, ukupno 137 u BiH |url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/u-sirokom-brijegu-potvrdjen-prvi-slucaj-koronavirusa-ukupno-137-u-bih/200324010 |website=Klix.ba |language=bs-BA}}</ref>\n| align=\"right\"| 27\n| align=\"right\"| 2\n| align=\"right\"| 0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" style=\"background:#EAECF0\"| [[Zenica-Doboj Canton]]\n| align=\"left\"| [[Breza, Bosnia and Herzegovina|Breza]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Potvr\u0111en prvi slu\u010daj koronavirusa u Brezi |url=http://ba.n1info.com/Vijesti/a418883/Potvrdjen-prvi-slucaj-koronavirusa-u-Brezi.html |website=N1 BA |language=bs-Latn-BA}}</ref>, [[Kakanj]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Prva tri slu\u010daja koronavirusa u Kaknju, povezani su sa zara\u017eenima u Tuzli |url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/prva-tri-slucaja-koronavirusa-u-kaknju-povezani-su-sa-zarazenima-u-tuzli/200330174 |website=Klix.ba |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=bs-BA}}</ref>, [[Te\u0161anj]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Potvr\u0111en prvi slu\u010daj Corona virusa na podru\u010dju op\u0107ine Te\u0161anj |url=http://www.radiotesanj.ba/contents/1608 |website=RADIO TE\u0160ANJ d.o.o.}}</ref> [[Visoko]],<ref>{{cite web |title=U Visokom potvr\u0111en prvi slu\u010daj koronavirusa, povezan sa slu\u010dajem iz Konjica |url=https://visoko.co.ba/u-visokom-potvrdjen-prvi-slucaj-koronavirusa-povezan-sa-slucajem-iz-konjica/ |website=Visoko.co.ba |language=bs-BA}}</ref> [[Zenica]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Potvr\u0111en prvi slu\u010daj korona virusa u Zenici |url=https://zenicainfo.ba/2020/03/09/potvrdjen-prvi-slucaj-korona-virusa-u-zenici/ |website=zenicainfo.ba |language=bs-BA |date=9 March 2020}}</ref> [[Zavidovi\u0107i]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Nova dva slu\u010daja koronavirusa u BiH: Jedan pacijent iz Zenice, drugi iz Zavidovi\u0107a |url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/nova-dva-slucaja-koronavirusa-u-bih-jedan-pacijent-iz-zenice-drugi-iz-zavidovica/200328141 |website=Klix.ba |accessdate=28 March 2020 |language=bs-BA}}</ref> [[\u017dep\u010de]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Jo\u0161 13 pozitivnih na koronavirus iz pet gradova u Bosni i Hercegovini |url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/jos-13-pozitivnih-na-koronavirus-iz-pet-gradova-u-bosni-i-hercegovini/200330007 |website=Klix.ba |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=bs-BA}}</ref>\n| align=\"right\"| 28\n| align=\"right\"| 0\n| align=\"right\"| 4\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\"| Total\n! align=\"right\"| 208\n! align=\"right\"| 9\n! align=\"right\"| 6\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\"|{{small|''As of 1 April 2020}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Dnevni izvje\u0161taj za potvr\u0111ene slu\u010dajeve COVID-19 U FBiH |url=https://www.zzjzfbih.ba/dnevni-izvjestaj-za-potvrdene-slucajeve-covid-19-u-fbih/ |website=ZZJZ FBiH }}</ref><ref name=\"covid-19.ba\" />\n|}\n\nAs of 31 March 2020, 6 people from [[Br\u010dko District]] have been infected.\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | \n! scope=\"col\" | Cases\n! scope=\"col\" | Deaths\n! scope=\"col\" | Recoveries\n|-\n| align=\"left\" style=\"background:#EAECF0\"| [[Br\u010dko District]]\n| align=\"right\"| 6\n| align=\"right\"| 0\n| align=\"right\"| 0\n| colspan=\"5\"|{{small|''As of 31 March 2020}}<ref name=\"Vlada Br\u010dko distrikta BiH\"/>\n|}\n\n==Measures==\n===Bosnia and Herzegovina===\n\nThe [[Presidency of Bosnia and Herzegovina]] announced Armed Forces' placement of quarantine tents at the country's borders intended for Bosnian citizens returning home. Every Bosnian citizen arriving to the country is obligated to self-quarantine for 14 days starting from the day of arrival.  Tents will be set up on the northern border with [[Croatia]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Dodik: Od ponedeljka vojska izlazi na granicu i postavlja satore za karantin | url= https://faktor.ba/vijest/dodik-od-ponedjeljka-vojska-izlazi-na-granicu-i-postavlja-satore-za-karantin/74164|website=faktor.ba | access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March 2020, Council of Ministers of Bosnia and Herzegovina issued a decision which forbids for foreign nationals entering Bosnia and Herzegovina to enter from areas with intensive transmission of virus coronas, and especially from: Provinces of the PRC (Wuhan), South Korea, Japan, Italy, Iran, France, Romania, Germany, Austria, Spain, Switzerland and Belgium.<ref>{{cite web |title=Vije\u0107e ministara BiH: Zabranjen ulazak strancima iz podru\u010dja sa intenzivnom transmisijom korona virusa |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/ba/balkan/vije%C4%87e-ministara-bih-zabranjen-ulazak-strancima-iz-podru%C4%8Dja-sa-intenzivnom-transmisijom-korona-virusa/1767130 |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March 2020, Council of Ministers of Bosnia and Herzegovina issued a decision which bans entrance for all foreigners, and also from 30 March 2020 all borders at [[List of airports in Bosnia and Herzegovina|airports in Bosnia and Herzegovina]] will be closed for passengers, and airplanes could land only to deliver [[cargo]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Vije\u0107e ministara BiH odlu\u010dilo: Privremeno se zatvaraju aerodromi za putnike u Bosni i Hercegovini |url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/vijece-ministara-bih-odlucilo-privremeno-se-zatvaraju-aerodromi-za-putnike-u-bosni-i-hercegovini/200324142 |website=Klix.ba |language=bs-BA}}</ref>\n\n===Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina===\n[[File:Triage tent Sarajevo.jpg|thumb|[[Triage]] tent located in Sarajevo during coronavirus pandemic.]]\nOn 11 March, the [[Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina]], had enacted a 2-week shutdown of all schools, high schools and universities in order to contain the spread of the virus,<ref>{{cite web |title=Na dvije sedmice se obustavlja nastava u \u0161kolama i na fakultetima u FBiH |url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/na-dvije-sedmice-se-obustavlja-nastava-u-skolama-i-na-fakultetima-u-fbih/200311085 |website=Klix.ba |accessdate=11 March 2020 |language=bs-BA}}</ref> which was later prolonged by all cantons.<ref>{{cite web |title=Nastava u Tuzlanskom kantonu \u0107e biti obustavljena do daljnjeg zbog koronavirusa |url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/nastava-u-tuzlanskom-kantonu-ce-biti-obustavljena-do-daljnjeg-zbog-koronavirusa/200326239 |website=Klix.ba |language=bs-BA}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina already had acts of profiteering. Fines have already been passed to local pharmacies and stores who used this situation and high demand for anti-bacterial gels/sprays and surgical masks. They lifted the prices as much as 3 times of the usual price.<ref>{{cite web | title= Apoteci u Sarajevu 10000km kazne zbog trostruko visih cijena|url=https://www.nesradio.com/novo/vijesti/novosti/Apoteci-u-Sarajevu-10000-KM-kazne-zbog-trostruko-visih-cijena/10723}}</ref> Federal inspection has given out fines in the sum of 43.500&nbsp;km (~22.000 Euros).<ref>{{cite web| title=BiH: Tr\u017ei\u0161ni inspektori izrekli 16 kazni zbog podizanja cijena|url=https://www.slobodnaevropa.org/a/30488933.html}}</ref>\n[[File:Makeshift hand sanitizers.jpg|thumb|One of many [[hand sanitizer]]s attached to a lamp post in [[Visoko]]]]\nThe Headquarters of Federation of B&H issued on 18 March an order that banned all public gatherings, suspending the operation of all catering facilities for the preparation and sale of food and beverages, restaurants, pizzerias, confectioneries, beauty salons, hookah bars, coffee bars, discos, tea shops, cafes, private dentists.<ref>{{cite web |title=Pro\u010ditajte naredbe: Zabranjuje se rad kafi\u0107a, objekata za masovno okupljanje... |url=http://ba.n1info.com/Vijesti/a417173/Procitajte-naredbe-Zabranjuje-se-rad-kafica-objekata-za-masovno-okupljanje.html |website=N1 BA |accessdate=18 March 2020 |language=bs-Latn-BA}}</ref><ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web |title=Covid-19.ba |url=https://covid-19.ba/dokumenti/civilna_zastita |website=covid-19.ba}}</ref>\n\nSome cities, such as [[Visoko]], installed [[hand sanitizer]]s through the city, in addition to frequent overnight disinfection of streets.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.visoko-rtv.ba/jkpvisoko-zavrsena-dezinfekcija-u-gradu-visoko/|title=JKP\"VISOKO\": ZAVR\u0160ENA DEZINFEKCIJA U GRADU VISOKO|last=Redakcija|date=2020-03-19|website=RTV VISOKO|language=bs-BA|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ba.n1info.com/Vijesti/a416511/Visoko-Pocelo-postavljanje-dozatora-na-javnim-povrsinama-za-dezinfekciju-ruku.html|title=Visoko: Po\u010delo postavljanje dozatora na javnim povr\u0161inama za dezinfekciju ruku|website=N1 BA|language=bs-Latn-BA|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\nThe civil protection service of Federation of B&H on 20 March 2020 issued an order, which banned the movement of people under the age of 18 and over 65 in the Federation of BiH.<ref>{{cite web |title=Zabrana kretanja osobama mla\u0111im od 18 godina i starijim od 65 u FBiH |url=https://www.slobodnaevropa.org/a/30499978.html |website=Radio Slobodna Evropa |accessdate=21 March 2020 |language=sh}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March 2020, a [[curfew]] was introduced for the entire Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina every day from 18:00 until 05:00, and its implementation started on 22 March 2020.<ref>{{cite web |title=Federalni \u0161tab donio naredbu: Od sutra nave\u010der zabrana kretanja od 18 do 5 sati |url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/federalni-stab-donio-naredbu-od-sutra-navecer-zabrana-kretanja-od-18-do-5-sati/200321099 |website=Klix.ba |accessdate=21 March 2020 |language=bs-BA}}</ref> On 29 March 2020, time for curfew was changed to 20:00 until 05:00.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n\n===Republika Srpska===\n[[File:Coronavirus street desinfection in Doboj.jpg|thumb|Coronavirus street disinfection in [[Doboj]].]]\n[[Republika Srpska]] was first to implement measures, beginning from cities of [[Banja Luka]] and [[Doboj]], where business hours were either limited or all business completely forbidden. The Ministry of Health and Social Security ordered the disinfection of all public spaces and property.<ref>{{cite web | title=Ministar zdravlja naredio dezinfekciju svih javnih objekata i povrsina u rs| url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/ministar-zdravlja-naredio-dezinfekciju-svih-javnih-objekata-i-povrsina-u-rs-u/200314046|language=sr-SR}}</ref> Student dormitories in the city of Banja Luka were evacuated for immediate disinfection.<ref>{{cite web|title=Iseljavaju se studentski domovi u Banja Luci|url=https://www.nezavisne.com/novosti/drustvo/Iseljavaju-se-studentski-domovi-u-Banjaluci/588914|language=sr-SR}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 March 2020, Republika Srpska had officially enacted a ban on all public gatherings, shut down all schools, and banned entry to all tourists coming from any of the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|COVID-19 infected countries across the world]] in order to contain the spread of the virus within the country.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bosnia bars entry to travelers from coronavirus-hit countries |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-bosnia/bosnias-serb-region-shuts-schools-bans-public-gatherings-over-coronavirus-idUSKBN20X2CA |website=Reuters |accessdate=11 March 2020 |language=en |date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nBetween 12 and 13 March, numerous cities have made decisions to limit the work of grocery stores, restaurants, caf\u00e9s and completely limit the work of gyms and fitness centers. Banja Luka,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/ba/balkan/banjaluka-uvela-vanredne-mjere-zbog-korona-virusa/1763688|title=Banjaluka uvela vanredne mjere zbog korona virusa|accessdate=Mar 18, 2020}}</ref> [[\u010celinac]], [[Prnjavor, Bosnia and Herzegovina|Prnjavor]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvk3.info/prnjavor-zbog-korona-virusa-skracenje-radnog-vremena-i-zabrana-rada-naredba-stupa-na-snagu-odmah/|title=Prnjavor: Zbog korona virusa skra\u0107enje radnog vremena i zabrana rada; Naredba stupa na snagu odmah (VIDEO)|date=Mar 13, 2020|website=Televizija K3|accessdate=Mar 18, 2020}}</ref> [[Mrkonji\u0107 Grad]] and Doboj<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://doboj.gov.ba/bs/stab-korona/|title=\u0160tab za vanredne situacije: Naredba o regulisanju rada trgovinskih i drugih objekata na teritoriji Grada Doboja|date=Mar 13, 2020|accessdate=Mar 18, 2020}}</ref> are some of the cities that made these restrictions.\n\nOn 15 March, Banja Luka has decided to close all restaurants and caf\u00e9s in the city, with the exception of drugstores, hotels and motels, where drugstores will be working until 22h and hotels will be working until 18h.<ref>{{cite web|title=Banja Luka uvela nove mjere za spre\u010davanje \u0161irenja korona virusa|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/ba/balkan/banjaluka-uvela-nove-mjere-za-spre%C4%8Davanje-%C5%A1irenja-korona-virusa/1767145|language=sr-SR}}</ref>\n\nThe Minister of Health and Social Security, Alen \u0160erani\u0107, reported that 2026 people are under surveillance in Republika Srpska. \u0160erani\u0107 also noted that only citizens arriving from abroad would be allowed the virus testing, and [[quarantine]] will be made mandatory.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u0160erani\u0107:2026 osoba pod nadzorom u RS. Ne dolazite na samovoljno testiranje.|url=http://ba.n1info.com/Vijesti/a416687/Seranic-2.026-osoba-pod-nadzorom-u-RS-ne-dolazite-samovoljno-na-testiranje.html|language=sr-SR}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March 2020, [[curfew]] was introduced in entire Republika Srpska every day from 20:00 until 05:00,<ref>{{cite web |title=Dodik: U RS se od ve\u010deras uvodi policijski sat |url=http://ba.n1info.com/Vijesti/a418241/Dodik-U-RS-se-od-veceras-uvodi-policijski-sat.html |website=N1 BA |accessdate=21 March 2020 |language=bs-Latn-BA}}</ref> and total ban of movement for people older that 65.<ref>{{cite web |title=Vi\u0161kovi\u0107: Ve\u010deras u 20 sati po\u010dinje policijski sat u RS |url=https://bhrt.ba/viskovic-od-danas-zabranjeno-kretanje-za-starije-od-65-godina-a-za-sve-od-20-00-do-5-sati/1117340/ |website=BHRT |language=bs-BA |date=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March 2020 the National Assembly declared the state of emergency in Republika Srpska.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bosnian Serb region declares state of emergency over coronavirus |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-bosnia/bosnian-serb-region-declares-state-of-emergency-over-coronavirus-idUSKBN21F0OQ |website=Reuters.com |accessdate=28 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== Br\u010dko District ===\n\nThe Government of [[Br\u010dko District]] is regularly adopting measures for control and prevention of coronavirus pandemic and publish them on their official website.<ref>{{cite web |title=Vlada Br\u010dko distrikta BiH |url=http://www.vlada.bdcentral.net/ |website=www.vlada.bdcentral.net |accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nSince 22 March 2020, it is prohibited in Br\u010dko District to gather and move in public places and open or closed public areas in a group of three or more persons throughout the day, and [[curfew]] was introduced in entire Br\u010dko District every day from 21:00 until 05:00.<ref>{{cite web |title=U Br\u010dkom na javnom mjestu zabranjeno kretanje tri i vi\u0161e osoba u grupi |url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/u-brckom-na-javnom-mjestu-zabranjeno-kretanje-tri-i-vise-osoba-u-grupi/200322116 |website=Klix.ba |accessdate=22 March 2020 |language=bs-BA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Vlada Br\u010dko distrikta BiH |url=http://www.vlada.bdcentral.net/Publication/Read/donesena-naredba-o-policijskom-casu-u-brckom |website=www.vlada.bdcentral.net |accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Impact ==\n[[File:Empty shelves in store.jpg|thumb|Empty shelves for flour in one store in [[Sarajevo]] as a result of panic buying.]]\nMembers of the Board of the Tourism and Hospitality Group of the Foreign Trade Chamber of Bosnia and Herzegovina have warned that the situation in tourism as a sector sensitive to global disruptions and the emergence of a new coronavirus strain could lead to the collapse of all entities operating in the tourism and hospitality sector.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kako \u0107e COVID-19 uticati na bh. turizam: Masovni otkazi dolazaka! |url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/vijesti/bosna-i-hercegovina/kako-ce-covid-19-uticati-na-bh-turizam-masovni-otkazi-dolazaka/369923 |website=Radio Sarajevo |accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nFrom 21 March, most of the sports activities were canceled across the entire country, including all football matches in all categories.<ref>{{cite web |title=Odgo\u0111ene utakmice BH Telecom Premijer lige i Kupa BiH |url=https://www.nfsbih.ba/vijesti/nogomet-m/bht-premijer-liga/odgodene-utakmice-bh-telecom-premijer-lige-i-kupa-bih/ |website=www.nfsbih.ba |accessdate=21 March 2020 |language=bs-ba}}</ref>\n\n== International aid ==\nThe countries and [[international organization]]s that have sent aid and funds to Bosnia and Herzegovina, to help fight the pandemic:\n\n* {{Flag|EU}} - The EU is considering two ways to assist Bosnia and Herzegovina, including quick support in provision of up to [[Euro|EUR]] 7 million worth of medical equipment and mid-term adjustment and enforcement of EU support in the amount of up to EUR 50 million for the economic development programmes.<ref>{{cite web |title=EU to assist BiH with provision of medical equipment and mitigation of the COVID-19 impact on the economy |url=https://europa.ba/?p=68202 |website=Europa.ba |accessdate=25 March 2020 |date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|Serbia}} - Serbia is assisting Republika Srpska in medicines, protective equipment, and vital clinical machines, and also is assisting entire Bosnia and Herzegovina with food including wheat, corn and soybeans.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sastanak sa srpskim \u010dlanom Predsedni\u0161tva Bosne i Hercegovine |url=https://www.predsednik.rs/lat/pres-centar/vesti/sastanak-sa-srpskim-clanom-predsednistva-bosne-i-hercegovine-28779 |website=Predsednik Republike Srbije |accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|Switzerland}} - On 23 March 2020, Embassy of Switzerland in Bosnia and Herzegovina informed Minister of Security that Switzerland has allocate 200,000 [[USD]] for assistance to Bosnia and Herzegovina.<ref>{{cite web |title=Na videokonferenciji sa ambasadorima i predstavnicima me\u0111unarodnih organizacija i agencija BiH dobila 7.200.000 eura |url=http://www.msb.gov.ba/vijesti/saopstenja/default.aspx?id=18580&langTag=bs-BA |website=www.msb.gov.ba |accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|Turkey}} - Turkey sent humanitarian aid on 24 March 2020 that include protective masks, gloves, protective suits and goggles to [[Red Cross Society of Bosnia and Herzegovina]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Stigla pomo\u0107 iz Turske: Solidarnost sa BiH u te\u0161kim vremenima {{!}} Sarajevo.ba |url=https://www.sarajevo.ba/bs/article/7676/stigla-pomoc-iz-turske-solidarnost-sa-bih-u-teskim-vremenima |website=www.sarajevo.ba |language=bs}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|UN}} - [[United Nations Development Programme]] in Bosnia and Herzegovina urgently financed procurement of 50,000 coronavirus test kits.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bosnia will get 50,000 new coronavirus tests, minister says |url=http://ba.n1info.com/English/NEWS/a418117/Bosnia-will-get-50-000-new-coronavirus-tests-minister-says.html |website=N1 BA |language=bs-Latn-BA}}</ref>\n* {{Flag|USA}} - US Government on 23 March 2020 donated medical materials and other important supplies to the [[Armed Forces of Bosnia and Herzegovina]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sarajevo |first1=US Embassy |title=The first batch of humanitarian assistance from the U.S. Government has arrived to assist the citizens of BiH.  Arriving via U.S. military aircraft and donated to the AFBiH were medical materials and other important supplies.pic.twitter.com/P4ePxJaf8i |url=https://twitter.com/USEmbassySJJ/status/1242071446270214144 |website=@USEmbassySJJ |language=en |date=23 March 2020}}</ref> [[United States Agency for International Development|USAID]] is donating [[United States dollar|$]]1.2 million to Bosnia and Herzegovina to help its laboratory systems, activate case-finding & monitoring, support experts, bolster awareness & community engagement and strengthen prevention.<ref>{{cite web |title=@USAID is donating $1.2 million to #BiH to help its laboratory systems, activate case-finding & monitoring, support experts, bolster awareness & community engagement and strengthen prevention.  #COVID19  #Coronavirus #USAinBiH @USAIDGH @USAIDMarkGreen @USAIDBGlick @USEmbassySJJpic.twitter.com/Z4gWRK364Q |url=https://twitter.com/USAIDBIH/status/1244528920512409600 |website=@USAIDBIH |accessdate=31 March 2020 |language=en |date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [https://covid-19.ba/ Official website of Government of the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina related to coronavirus pandemic]\n* [https://koronavirususrpskoj.com/ Official website of Government of Republika Srpska related to coronavirus pandemic]\n\n{{Portal bar|Medicine|Europe|Bosnia and Herzegovina}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Bosnia and Herzegovina| ]]\n[[Category:2020 in Bosnia and Herzegovina|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Health in Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n", "name_user": "Smooth O", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMunicipalities and Cantons affected", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Bosnia_and_Herzegovina"}
{"title_page": "The Rain in Spain", "text_new": "{{for|information about rain in Spain|Climate of Spain}}\n{{Refimprove|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = The Rain in Spain\n| cover      = File:Julie Andrews Rex Harrison Robert Coote My Fair Lady.JPG\n| alt        =\n| caption    = [[Julie Andrews]] as Eliza, [[Rex Harrison]] as Higgins, [[Robert Coote]] as Pickering in \"The Rain in Spain\" segment, 1957\n| type       =\n| artist     =\n| album      =\n| EP         =\n| written    =\n| published  = 1956\n| released   =\n| format     =\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Musical theatre]]\n| length     =\n| label      =\n| writer     =\n| composer   = [[Frederick Loewe]]\n| lyricist   = [[Alan Jay Lerner]]\n| producer   =\n| chronology = Songs from the film ''[[My Fair Lady]]''\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| title      =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| prev_track =\n| track_no   =\n| next_track =\n| tracks     = {{My Fair Lady song chronology}}\n}}\n\"'''The Rain in Spain'''\" is a song from the [[musical theatre|musical]] ''[[My Fair Lady]]'', with music by [[Frederick Loewe]] and lyrics by [[Alan Jay Lerner]]. The song was published in [[1956 in music|1956]], sounding similar to [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9w5TXAR1oVc piano trio in C minor 3rd movement by Josep Suk].{{fact|date=July 2019}}\n\nThe song is a turning point in the plotline of the musical. Professor Higgins and Colonel Pickering have been drilling [[Eliza Doolittle]] incessantly with speech exercises, trying to break her [[Cockney accent]] speech pattern. The key lyric in the song is \"The rain in Spain stays mainly in the plain\", which contains five words that a Cockney would pronounce with {{IPA|[\u00e6\u026a]}} or {{IPA|[a\u026a]}}<ref>{{Cite book\n|last=Wells\n|first=John C.\n|authorlink=John C. Wells\n|year=1982\n|pages=307\u2013308\n|title=Accents of English 2: The British Isles\n|place=Cambridge\n|publisher=Cambridge University Press\n|isbn=0-521-24224-X\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=a3-ElL71fikC\n|ref=harv\n}}</ref> \u2013 more like \"eye\" {{IPA|[a\u026a]}} than the [[Received Pronunciation]] diphthong {{IPA|[e\u026a]}}. With the three of them nearly exhausted, Eliza finally \"gets it\", and recites the sentence with all \"proper\" long-As. The trio breaks into song, repeating this key phrase as well as singing other exercises correctly, such as \"In Hertford, Hereford, and Hampshire, hurricanes hardly happen\", in which Eliza had failed before by [[H-dropping|dropping]] the leading 'H'.\n\n==Origin==\nThe phrase does not appear in Shaw's original play ''[[Pygmalion (play)|Pygmalion]]'', on which ''My Fair Lady'' is based, but it is used in the [[Pygmalion (1938 film)|1938 film of the play]]. According to ''The Disciple and His Devil'', the biography of [[Gabriel Pascal]] by his wife Valerie, it was he who introduced the famous phonetic exercises \"The rain in Spain stays mainly in the plain\" and \"In Hertford, Hereford, and Hampshire, hurricanes hardly ever happen\" into the script of the film, both of which were later used in the song in ''My Fair Lady''.<ref>Pascal, Valerie, \"The Disciple and His Devil,\" ''McGraw-hill'', 1970. p. 83.</ref>\n\n== In other languages ==\nThe musical has been translated into many languages, with Eliza speaking Berlin, Vienna, Stockholm, G\u00f6teborg, Amsterdam, and Budapest dialects.{{cn|date=October 2019}} Versions of \"The rain in Spain stays mainly in the plain\" in various languages include:\n*Hebrew: \"{{Hebrew|\u05d1\u05e8\u05d3 \u05d9\u05e8\u05d3 \u05d1\u05d3\u05e8\u05d5\u05dd \u05e1\u05e4\u05e8\u05d3 \u05d4\u05e2\u05e8\u05d1}}\" (\"Barad yarad bidrom sfarad haerev\": Hail fell in southern Spain this evening.)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mfa.gov.il/MFA/MFAArchive/1990_1999/1998/11/The%20Rain%20in%20Spain|title=Almagor, Dan, \"\"Barad yarad bidrom sfarad: How \"The Rain in Spain\" Fell in Eretz-Israel,\" Israel Review of Arts and Letters, Israel Ministry of Foreign Affairs (MFA.org), November 19, 1998.|website=Mfa.gov.il|accessdate=9 October 2018}}</ref>\n*Hungarian: \"Lenn d\u00e9len \u00e9des \u00e9jen \u00e9dent rem\u00e9lsz.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicalmuzeum.hu/indexmc.php?p=969&t=59|title=Dilatato corde - Sz\u00e1rnyal\u00f3 sz\u00edvvel - Dud\u00e1s R\u00f3bert Gyula - N\u00e9mo honlapja ~ Musicalm\u00fazeum|website=Musicalmuzeum.hu|accessdate=9 October 2018}}</ref>\n*Dutch: \"Het Spaanse graan heeft de orkaan doorstaan.\" (The Spanish grain has survived the storm.)\n*Spanish: \"La lluvia en Sevilla es una pura maravilla\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sevilla.abc.es/sevilla/20131008/sevi-refranes-lluvia-sevilla-maravilla-201310071226.html|title=Origen del dicho: \u00abLa lluvia en Sevilla es una maravilla\u00bb|access-date=2020-03-10|date=2013-10-07|website=sevilla|lang=es}}</ref> (The rain in Spain is a true marvel) playing with the sound of the \"ll\".\n*Danish: \"En snegl p\u00e5 vejen er tegn p\u00e5 regn i Spanien.\" (A snail on the road is a sign of rain in Spain). This is a play on the pronunciation of the diphthong in \"snegl\", \"vejen\", \"tegn\", and \"regn\" in the lower Copenhagen sociolect of the 1950's.\n\n==Usage in other popular culture==\n{{reduce trivia|section|date=June 2017}}\n*A 1985 British television commercial for [[Heineken]] parodies the scene. [[Sylvestra Le Touzel]] plays a woman who speaks posh, and after a drink of Heineken a [[cockney]] accent appears. It was ranked at number 9 in Campaign Live's 2008 list of the \"Top 10 Funniest TV Ads of All Time\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/news/865453/ |title=The Top 10 funniest TV ads of all time |publisher=Campaignlive.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-08-12}}</ref> and at number 29 in [[Channel 4]]'s list of the \"[[100 Greatest (UK TV series)|100 Greatest TV Ads]]\" in 2000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/greatest_ads/|title=The 100 Greatest TV Ads|year=2000|publisher=[[Channel 4]]|location=London|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010618095141/http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/greatest_ads/|archive-date=18 June 2001|url-status=dead|access-date=5 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n*In the ''[[Family Guy]]'' episode \"[[One If by Clam, Two If by Sea]]\", Stewie tries to teach a girl to lose her Cockney accent. Together, he and Eliza sing a parody, \"The Life of The Wife is Ended by the Knife.\"<ref>The Internet Movie Transcriptions Database, \"[http://www.movietranscriptions.com/240200_Family_Guy_S3_E111.html#p1210 Family Guy S3 E1-11].\"</ref><ref>Planet Family Guy, \"[http://www.planet-familyguy.com/pfg/subtitles/34/ Subtitle Scripts] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120914050259/http://www.planet-familyguy.com/pfg/subtitles/34/ |date=2012-09-14 }}.\"</ref>\n*The satirical revue ''[[Forbidden Broadway]]'' set up playwright [[David Mamet]] as being exasperated with [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna's]] acting style with the lyrics, \"I strain in vain to train Madonna's brain.\"<ref>Kilian, Michael, \"[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/chicagotribune/access/24583195.html?dids=24583195:24583195&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Nov+6%2C+1988&author=Michael+Kilian&pub=Chicago+Tribune+%28pre-1997+Fulltext%29&edition=&startpage=28&desc=OFFING+BROADWAY+SATIRICAL+REVUE+GROWS+INTO+A+STAR-BASHING+BIGGIE Offing Broadway Satirical Revue Grows Into A Star-Bashing Biggie],\" ''Chicago Tribune'', 6 November 1988, p. 28. [http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1988-11-25/lifestyle/0080350265_1_lupone-forbidden-broadway-carol-channing/2 (Full Text)]</ref><ref>Kuchwara, Michael, \"[http://cox.lubbockonline.com/stories/030500/ent_030500037.shtml Alessandrini zeroes in on next Broadway target ],\" Knight-Ridder, 5 March 2000.</ref> The song is included on the album ''[[Forbidden Broadway, Vol. 2]]''.\n*''[[The Simpsons]]'' episode \"[[My Fair Laddy]]\" is itself a parody of ''My Fair Lady'', and includes the song \"Not On My Clothes\" (with the lyrics, \"What flows from the nose does not go on my clothes\").<ref>Clausen, Alf and Michael Price, \"[http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/scorch.asp?ppn=SC0085491 Not On My Clothes],\" T C F Music Publishing, Inc., 2006.</ref>\n*In [[Stephen King]]'s book, ''[[The Dark Tower: The Gunslinger|The Gunslinger]],'' he writes a parody titled The Rain in Spain Falls Mainly on the Plain. King's novel ''[[Salem's Lot]]'' also features his changed lyrics recited by Mark Petrie.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Salem's Lot|author=Stephen King|publisher=Random House|year=2011|pages=653|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6OxSHEbM1isC&pg=PA369}}</ref>\n*In 2012, a punk rock version of \"The Rain in Spain\" was featured in comedy-musical TV series ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'', episode \"[[Choke (Glee)|Choke]]\". The song was performed by [[Mark Salling]] (as his character [[Puck (Glee)|Puck]]) and the guys of the series' fictional glee club New Directions.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://top40.about.com/od/top10lists/tp/Glee-Songs-Report-Card-Season-3-Episode-18.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-03-27 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160113095726/http://top40.about.com/od/top10lists/tp/Glee-Songs-Report-Card-Season-3-Episode-18.htm |archivedate=2016-01-13 }}</ref>\n*In the 1956\u201359 revue ''[[At the Drop of a Hat]]'', [[Michael Flanders]] observes in a brief comic monologue that: \"Despite all you may have heard to the contrary, the rain in Spain stays almost invariably in the hills.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nyanko.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/fas/hat_weath.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140517060316/http://www.nyanko.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/fas/hat_weath.html |archive-date=2014-05-17 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.mfa.gov.il/MFA/MFAArchive/1990_1999/1998/7/The%20Rain%20in%20Spain ''\"Barad yarad bidrom sfarad\": How \"The Rain in Spain\" Fell in Eretz-Israel'', by Dan Almagor]\n* {{YouTube|AenLJ75dBl4|\"The Rain in Spain\" from \"My Fair Lady\"}}, ''[[My Fair Lady#2001 London revival.3B 2003 Hollywood Bowl production|2001 London revival]]''\n* {{YouTube|3a6lz6IS5P4|\"The Rain in Spain (My Fair Lady)\" from \"Hey Mr Producer\"|link=no}}, ''1998 live recording of \"[[Hey, Mr. Producer!]]\"''\n* {{YouTube|t2NBP67KZbw|\"The Rain in Spain\" from \"An Evening with Alan Jay Lerner\"|link=no}}, ''1987 live recording of \"An Evening with Alan Jay Lerner\"'' (feat. [[Pl\u00e1cido Domingo]], [[Liz Robertson]], [[Richard Caldicot]])\n* {{MetroLyrics song|my-fair-lady|the-rain-in-spain}}\n{{My Fair Lady|state=expanded}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rain in Spain, The}}\n[[Category:Phonetics]]\n[[Category:Songs with music by Frederick Loewe]]\n[[Category:Songs with lyrics by Alan Jay Lerner]]\n[[Category:Songs from My Fair Lady]]\n[[Category:1956 songs]]\n[[Category:Songs about Spain]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|information about rain in Spain|Climate of Spain}}\n{{Refimprove|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = The Rain in Spain\n| cover      = File:Julie Andrews Rex Harrison Robert Coote My Fair Lady.JPG\n| alt        =\n| caption    = [[Julie Andrews]] as Eliza, [[Rex Harrison]] as Higgins, [[Robert Coote]] as Pickering in \"The Rain in Spain\" segment, 1957\n| type       =\n| artist     =\n| album      =\n| EP         =\n| written    =\n| published  = 1956\n| released   =\n| format     =\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Musical theatre]]\n| length     =\n| label      =\n| writer     =\n| composer   = [[Frederick Loewe]]\n| lyricist   = [[Alan Jay Lerner]]\n| producer   =\n| chronology = Songs from the film ''[[My Fair Lady]]''\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| title      =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| prev_track =\n| track_no   =\n| next_track =\n| tracks     = {{My Fair Lady song chronology}}\n}}\n\"'''The Rain in Spain'''\" is a song from the [[musical theatre|musical]] ''[[My Fair Lady]]'', with music by [[Frederick Loewe]] and lyrics by [[Alan Jay Lerner]]. The song was published in [[1956 in music|1956]], sounding similar to [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9w5TXAR1oVc piano trio in C minor 3rd movement by Josep Suk].{{fact|date=July 2019}}\n\nThe song is a turning point in the plotline of the musical. Professor Higgins and Colonel Pickering have been drilling [[Eliza Doolittle]] incessantly with speech exercises, trying to break her [[Cockney accent]] speech pattern. The key lyric in the song is \"The rain in Spain stays mainly in the plain\", which contains five words that a Cockney would pronounce with {{IPA|[\u00e6\u026a]}} or {{IPA|[a\u026a]}}<ref>{{Cite book\n|last=Wells\n|first=John C.\n|authorlink=John C. Wells\n|year=1982\n|pages=307\u2013308\n|title=Accents of English 2: The British Isles\n|place=Cambridge\n|publisher=Cambridge University Press\n|isbn=0-521-24224-X\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=a3-ElL71fikC\n|ref=harv\n}}</ref> \u2013 more like \"eye\" {{IPA|[a\u026a]}} than the [[Received Pronunciation]] diphthong {{IPA|[e\u026a]}}. With the three of them nearly exhausted, Eliza finally \"gets it\", and recites the sentence with all \"proper\" long-As. The trio breaks into song, repeating this key phrase as well as singing other exercises correctly, such as \"In Hertford, Hereford, and Hampshire, hurricanes hardly happen\", in which Eliza had failed before by [[H-dropping|dropping]] the leading 'H'.\n\n==Origin==\nThe phrase does not appear in Shaw's original play ''[[Pygmalion (play)|Pygmalion]]'', on which ''My Fair Lady'' is based, but it is used in the [[Pygmalion (1938 film)|1938 film of the play]]. According to ''The Disciple and His Devil'', the biography of [[Gabriel Pascal]] by his wife Valerie, it was he who introduced the famous phonetic exercises \"The rain in Spain stays mainly in the plain\" and \"In Hertford, Hereford, and Hampshire, hurricanes hardly ever happen\" into the script of the film, both of which were later used in the song in ''My Fair Lady''.<ref>Pascal, Valerie, \"The Disciple and His Devil,\" ''McGraw-hill'', 1970. p. 83.</ref>\n\n== In other languages ==\nThe musical has been translated into many languages, with Eliza speaking Berlin, Vienna, Stockholm, G\u00f6teborg, Amsterdam, and Budapest dialects.{{cn|date=October 2019}} Versions of \"The rain in Spain stays mainly in the plain\" in various languages include:\n*Hebrew: \"{{Hebrew|\u05d1\u05e8\u05d3 \u05d9\u05e8\u05d3 \u05d1\u05d3\u05e8\u05d5\u05dd \u05e1\u05e4\u05e8\u05d3 \u05d4\u05e2\u05e8\u05d1}}\" (\"Barad yarad bidrom sfarad haerev\": Hail fell in southern Spain this evening.)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mfa.gov.il/MFA/MFAArchive/1990_1999/1998/11/The%20Rain%20in%20Spain|title=Almagor, Dan, \"\"Barad yarad bidrom sfarad: How \"The Rain in Spain\" Fell in Eretz-Israel,\" Israel Review of Arts and Letters, Israel Ministry of Foreign Affairs (MFA.org), November 19, 1998.|website=Mfa.gov.il|accessdate=9 October 2018}}</ref>\n*Hungarian: \"Lenn d\u00e9len \u00e9des \u00e9jen \u00e9dent rem\u00e9lsz.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicalmuzeum.hu/indexmc.php?p=969&t=59|title=Dilatato corde - Sz\u00e1rnyal\u00f3 sz\u00edvvel - Dud\u00e1s R\u00f3bert Gyula - N\u00e9mo honlapja ~ Musicalm\u00fazeum|website=Musicalmuzeum.hu|accessdate=9 October 2018}}</ref>\n*Dutch: \"Het Spaanse graan heeft de orkaan doorstaan.\" (The Spanish grain has survived the storm.)\n*Spanish: \"La lluvia en Sevilla es una pura maravilla\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sevilla.abc.es/sevilla/20131008/sevi-refranes-lluvia-sevilla-maravilla-201310071226.html|title=Origen del dicho: \u00abLa lluvia en Sevilla es una maravilla\u00bb|access-date=2020-03-10|date=2013-10-07|website=sevilla|lang=es}}</ref> (The rain in Spain is a true marvel) playing with the sound of the \"ll\".\n\n==Usage in other popular culture==\n{{reduce trivia|section|date=June 2017}}\n*A 1985 British television commercial for [[Heineken]] parodies the scene. [[Sylvestra Le Touzel]] plays a woman who speaks posh, and after a drink of Heineken a [[cockney]] accent appears. It was ranked at number 9 in Campaign Live's 2008 list of the \"Top 10 Funniest TV Ads of All Time\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.campaignlive.co.uk/news/865453/ |title=The Top 10 funniest TV ads of all time |publisher=Campaignlive.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2015-08-12}}</ref> and at number 29 in [[Channel 4]]'s list of the \"[[100 Greatest (UK TV series)|100 Greatest TV Ads]]\" in 2000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/greatest_ads/|title=The 100 Greatest TV Ads|year=2000|publisher=[[Channel 4]]|location=London|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010618095141/http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/greatest_ads/|archive-date=18 June 2001|url-status=dead|access-date=5 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n*In the ''[[Family Guy]]'' episode \"[[One If by Clam, Two If by Sea]]\", Stewie tries to teach a girl to lose her Cockney accent. Together, he and Eliza sing a parody, \"The Life of The Wife is Ended by the Knife.\"<ref>The Internet Movie Transcriptions Database, \"[http://www.movietranscriptions.com/240200_Family_Guy_S3_E111.html#p1210 Family Guy S3 E1-11].\"</ref><ref>Planet Family Guy, \"[http://www.planet-familyguy.com/pfg/subtitles/34/ Subtitle Scripts] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120914050259/http://www.planet-familyguy.com/pfg/subtitles/34/ |date=2012-09-14 }}.\"</ref>\n*The satirical revue ''[[Forbidden Broadway]]'' set up playwright [[David Mamet]] as being exasperated with [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna's]] acting style with the lyrics, \"I strain in vain to train Madonna's brain.\"<ref>Kilian, Michael, \"[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/chicagotribune/access/24583195.html?dids=24583195:24583195&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Nov+6%2C+1988&author=Michael+Kilian&pub=Chicago+Tribune+%28pre-1997+Fulltext%29&edition=&startpage=28&desc=OFFING+BROADWAY+SATIRICAL+REVUE+GROWS+INTO+A+STAR-BASHING+BIGGIE Offing Broadway Satirical Revue Grows Into A Star-Bashing Biggie],\" ''Chicago Tribune'', 6 November 1988, p. 28. [http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1988-11-25/lifestyle/0080350265_1_lupone-forbidden-broadway-carol-channing/2 (Full Text)]</ref><ref>Kuchwara, Michael, \"[http://cox.lubbockonline.com/stories/030500/ent_030500037.shtml Alessandrini zeroes in on next Broadway target ],\" Knight-Ridder, 5 March 2000.</ref> The song is included on the album ''[[Forbidden Broadway, Vol. 2]]''.\n*''[[The Simpsons]]'' episode \"[[My Fair Laddy]]\" is itself a parody of ''My Fair Lady'', and includes the song \"Not On My Clothes\" (with the lyrics, \"What flows from the nose does not go on my clothes\").<ref>Clausen, Alf and Michael Price, \"[http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/scorch.asp?ppn=SC0085491 Not On My Clothes],\" T C F Music Publishing, Inc., 2006.</ref>\n*In [[Stephen King]]'s book, ''[[The Dark Tower: The Gunslinger|The Gunslinger]],'' he writes a parody titled The Rain in Spain Falls Mainly on the Plain. King's novel ''[[Salem's Lot]]'' also features his changed lyrics recited by Mark Petrie.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Salem's Lot|author=Stephen King|publisher=Random House|year=2011|pages=653|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6OxSHEbM1isC&pg=PA369}}</ref>\n*In 2012, a punk rock version of \"The Rain in Spain\" was featured in comedy-musical TV series ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]'', episode \"[[Choke (Glee)|Choke]]\". The song was performed by [[Mark Salling]] (as his character [[Puck (Glee)|Puck]]) and the guys of the series' fictional glee club New Directions.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://top40.about.com/od/top10lists/tp/Glee-Songs-Report-Card-Season-3-Episode-18.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-03-27 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160113095726/http://top40.about.com/od/top10lists/tp/Glee-Songs-Report-Card-Season-3-Episode-18.htm |archivedate=2016-01-13 }}</ref>\n*In the 1956\u201359 revue ''[[At the Drop of a Hat]]'', [[Michael Flanders]] observes in a brief comic monologue that: \"Despite all you may have heard to the contrary, the rain in Spain stays almost invariably in the hills.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nyanko.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/fas/hat_weath.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140517060316/http://www.nyanko.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/fas/hat_weath.html |archive-date=2014-05-17 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.mfa.gov.il/MFA/MFAArchive/1990_1999/1998/7/The%20Rain%20in%20Spain ''\"Barad yarad bidrom sfarad\": How \"The Rain in Spain\" Fell in Eretz-Israel'', by Dan Almagor]\n* {{YouTube|AenLJ75dBl4|\"The Rain in Spain\" from \"My Fair Lady\"}}, ''[[My Fair Lady#2001 London revival.3B 2003 Hollywood Bowl production|2001 London revival]]''\n* {{YouTube|3a6lz6IS5P4|\"The Rain in Spain (My Fair Lady)\" from \"Hey Mr Producer\"|link=no}}, ''1998 live recording of \"[[Hey, Mr. Producer!]]\"''\n* {{YouTube|t2NBP67KZbw|\"The Rain in Spain\" from \"An Evening with Alan Jay Lerner\"|link=no}}, ''1987 live recording of \"An Evening with Alan Jay Lerner\"'' (feat. [[Pl\u00e1cido Domingo]], [[Liz Robertson]], [[Richard Caldicot]])\n* {{MetroLyrics song|my-fair-lady|the-rain-in-spain}}\n{{My Fair Lady|state=expanded}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rain in Spain, The}}\n[[Category:Phonetics]]\n[[Category:Songs with music by Frederick Loewe]]\n[[Category:Songs with lyrics by Alan Jay Lerner]]\n[[Category:Songs from My Fair Lady]]\n[[Category:1956 songs]]\n[[Category:Songs about Spain]]\n", "name_user": "Jens Brix Christiansen", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eIn other languages:Added Danish", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Rain_in_Spain"}
